column5: Hi all,  Went out with my neighbour in his small tinny the other day. It took us longer to get there than it did to get a limit and that's just fine…win/win! Get to mess around in the great outdoors and experience awesome fishing.  I'm pretty lucky to have such a great neighbour, top bloke!         PS….Thanks Joeytier for helping me decide where to go that day, your back lake adventures were the inspiration for this one and the reason we tried a smaller lake.
On that twisty thing eh? LOL  Nice Bloke indeed Simon.
Your listening to more country/folk/twang lately.  Yep, great neighbor
Don't have to have a $20000 boat to have a blast.  Well done

Totally missed this. Awesome!  YOU INSPIRED THIS POST GODDAMIT>>>>>LOL  Your listening to more country/folk/twang lately.  Yep, great neighbor  LOL...you noticed. Its more to do with what music is available to use on 'monetized' videos on youtube. I finally discovered in May this year, after 8 years of making videos that Youtube will pay me, only catch is I cant choose copyrighted material or they wont pay me, I aint making millions but have made about $700 in 6 months, keeps me in minnows....just!  Don't have to have a $20000 boat to have a blast.  Well done   LOL...my neighbour has a $30000 boat, and that little tinny!
So you're a prostaffer now???  You better not be wearing a YouTube jersey in the next video!

So you're a prostaffer now??? You better not be wearing a YouTube jersey in the next video!   LOL…..no…just doing what Ive always done for no gian other than my own enjoyment and sharing adventures with y'all,  and then someone told me I could make a few shillings doing it without really lifting a finger….just my kind of gig! won't sellout, won't compromise…smash capitalism!!!!! LOL.
